Comment (src/components/users/UserRolesPanel.vue:259):
**Low / nit — error extraction can throw on a non-standard error body.**

`errorResponse.response?.data.errors.body` only optional-chains `response`. If `response` is present but `response.data` is absent or not the `{errors:{body}}` shape (e.g. an empty/HTML 5xx body, where axios sets `data` to `''`), then `.errors.body` throws a `TypeError` *inside* the catch block. The function's promise then rejects un-awaited (called from `@submit.prevent`), so the dialog stays open with no `assignError` shown — a silent failure.

This matches the existing codebase convention (UserView/GroupView/GroupMembersPanel use the same shape) and the API reliably returns `{errors:{body}}`, so risk is low. Hardening suggestion: `errorResponse.response?.data?.errors?.body`. Same applies to `removeRole` (~line 278) here and to both handlers in `GroupRolesPanel.vue` (~lines 236, 253).
Replies:
**lisa implementation guidance:** Agreed — hardening the error extraction to fully optional-chain. Will change `errorResponse.response?.data.errors.body` → `errorResponse.response?.data?.errors?.body` in all four handlers: UserRolesPanel.vue assignRole + removeRole, and GroupRolesPanel.vue assignRole + removeRole. Prevents a TypeError inside the catch (which would otherwise reject the @submit.prevent handler un-awaited and leave the dialog open with no assignError shown).

